    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>I needed a functionality in Drupal that handles the notifications for users based on role on new content in the website, so I looked around and considered <a href="https://drupal.org/project/notifications" target="_blank">Notifications Module</a> which is great, but adds much more than I really need for a simply notify module.</p>

<p>Role Notify is a light-weight module to work as an alternative module for simple notifications.Â It basically helps you notify all registered users of a selected role when a new content is published in the site.</p>

<p>Notifications can be selective with different settings on each content type. Users can choose whether to notify on the node level.</p>

